Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.09,0:00:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Waiting gets us nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.47,0:00:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a step forward into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.85,0:00:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a deduction and love countdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.81,0:00:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Standing in for Kogorou is the high-school detective girl, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.14,0:00:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's resolve the mystery of the vanished murder weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.90,0:00:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.02,0:00:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.54,0:01:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the Mizunashi Rena case...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.54,0:02:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hondou Eisuke had been protected by the FBI, but he's returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.59,0:02:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we went to a karaoke box to celebrate his return...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.84,0:02:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were shadowed by a suspicious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.72,0:02:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an3}Could he be an FBI agent observing and guarding Eisuke?\h
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.81,0:02:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, that man was murdered in a room at the karaoke box.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.15,0:02:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is one of the customers who came to sing karaoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.24,0:02:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be Eisuke?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.38,0:02:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, first of all...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.97,0:02:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll start with Tamai Kunio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from room #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.59,0:02:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.10,0:02:53.14,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I came here today on the way back from fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:53.14,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}\h\h\h\hTamai Kunio (63)\h\h\h\h\N\h\hRoom #1 Customer\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.93,0:02:57.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You came to sing, karaoke alone after fishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.35,0:02:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.15,0:03:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure caught a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.03,0:03:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell the truth, those are mostly fish I bought at the supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.87,0:03:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I carelessly let my fishing rod drift away...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.66,0:03:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'd promised my family that I'd bring back a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.71,0:03:22.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I had no choice but to buy the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.09,0:03:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True enough, there's no rod inside this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.18,0:03:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they'd be suspicious if I came home too early...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.10,0:03:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just wasting time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.77,0:03:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next is Honma Kyouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from room #2.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.90,0:03:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.35,0:03:50.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As for me, my company is having a karaoke\Ntournament soon, so I came here to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.99,0:03:50.20,CharCard02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}\h\hHonma Kyouta (32)\h\h\N\h\hRoom #2 Customer\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.78,0:03:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your company in this area?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.12,0:03:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be embarrassed if my co-workers knew about this, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I deliberately came here where it was far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:07.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You buy cigarettes by the carton?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's because I'm a heavy smoker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose you can't use cigarettes to bludgeon someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.81,0:04:26.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you came to sing karaoke on the way home from school?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.30,0:04:28.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:28.19,CharCard03,,0,0,0,,\h\hHondou Eisuke (17)\h\h\N\h\hRoom #3 Customer\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.90,0:04:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young people these days...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.03,0:04:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, maracas!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.45,0:04:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like these a lot myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.42,0:04:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it couldn't have been maracas either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.02,0:04:49.70,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next we have Arimoto Konji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from room #4.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.38,0:04:49.93,CharCard04,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}\h\h\hAromoto Konji (34)\h\h\h\N\h\hRoom #4 Customer\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.22,0:04:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came to sing karaoke with my girlfriend\Non the way back from the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.93,0:04:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not a problem, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.10,0:05:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this that carbonated beverage that came out a bit ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.81,0:05:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she wanted to try it, so I bought some.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.44,0:05:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It tasted awful, so she only had one sip.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.07,0:05:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would have been impossible with a PET bottle also.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.37,0:05:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've checked out everyone's rooms, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:25.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked the restrooms too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That shouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.59,0:05:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It absolutely must be somewhere in this karaoke box...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.26,0:05:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some weapon, like a bludgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.26,0:05:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I need to check if the\Nmurdered man was an FBI agent or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.69,0:05:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would Jodie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s phone not be connecting?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.90,0:05:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.36,0:05:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've just finished developing the film that the victim had.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.74,0:05:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It shows something we didn't expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.91,0:06:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something we didn't expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.54,0:06:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, what's this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There all of us! Eww!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean he was a stalker?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.67,0:06:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure looks that way. Icky!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it looks like it doesn't have anything to do with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.72,0:06:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.97,0:06:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't even see the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.93,0:06:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you all didn't even pass by the victim in the corridor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.48,0:06:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.98,0:06:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we had met, it would have been either\Nin the corridor or in the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.02,0:06:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't see anyone except for these people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.48,0:06:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't see any of the other customers until the incident occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.07,0:06:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if you consider it normally...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.08,0:06:45.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the culprit that boy with the round glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.66,0:06:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.04,0:06:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was being followed by the stalker and\Nlost control and killed him or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.79,0:06:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.76,0:06:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, look carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.14,0:07:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't each of these pictures have me in the center?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.10,0:07:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means I was the target, not this geeky glasses boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.61,0:07:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.11,0:07:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you let us go home already, Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.65,0:07:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Mr. Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.36,0:07:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that Sonoko is the focus of every picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.41,0:07:26.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, perhaps the murdered man wasn't with the FBI?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.16,0:07:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.75,0:07:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.25,0:07:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already 7:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.29,0:07:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I can't let you leave yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.72,0:07:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't mind hanging around here until I'm cleared of suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please do that, definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just happened to bring some cards with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.81,0:07:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can kill time playing poker or blackjack with my girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.69,0:07:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blackjack!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.40,0:07:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had forgotten about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:07:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.49,0:08:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Based on the presumed time of death of Moniwa Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho was beaten to death in room #5 of this karaoke box...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.45,0:08:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crime was committed in an approximate thirty minute\Nwindow, likely between 6:00 and 6:20 this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.21,0:08:22.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the recording made by the security camera, the people\Nwho passed by the victim's room in those 30 minutes were:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.76,0:08:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honma Kyouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who came out of room #2 at 5:50.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.73,0:08:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hondou Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, who came out of room #3 at 6:03.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.73,0:08:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arimoto Konji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who came out of room #4 at 6:05.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.99,0:08:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Tamai Kunio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who came out of\Nroom #1 at 6:07, making 4 people in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.28,0:08:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is definitely one of you four.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's why I can't let you leave yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the murder weapon hasn't been found anywhere, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.04,0:08:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you said it was some kind of blunt weapon, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.17,0:09:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure that if you can't find it, you might\Nbe overstepping by making us remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.51,0:09:10.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here, the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.81,0:09:14.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it's something that wouldn't appear to be a weapon at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.52,0:09:19.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko, it happened! Just like always!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.19,0:09:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. That wasn't me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.58,0:09:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.62,0:09:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.71,0:09:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a case this simple, I thought it wasn't me who would solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.42,0:09:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you all really don't understand, then I'll explain it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.22,0:09:48.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trick that, after the crime,{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged the shape\Nof the murder weapon and made it vanish...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.47,0:09:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the culprit who used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.94,0:10:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, if it's OK with you, could you please tell us about it, young lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.51,0:10:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.53,0:10:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You 're saying there was a blunt weapon at the time of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.43,0:10:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now it's disappeared, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.76,0:10:12.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.86,0:10:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I know what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.41,0:10:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer weapon was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.22,0:10:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A gigantic block of ice!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.38,0:10:24.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so the culprit is the one who had a cooler that\Ncould preserve it for a long period of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.17,0:10:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamai Kunio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.18,0:10:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.01,0:10:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bzzz. Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.18,0:10:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that if ice was used, it could be melted\Nafter the crime and would disappear, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.52,0:10:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was used to strike with, there should be pieces of ice, scattered\Nwater droplets, and a water stain left behind at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there weren't any stains like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since we can still see the splattered blood from the corpse,\Nthere's no evidence that the culprit wiped the floor after the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:10:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead, the culprit placed something\Nhard inside a certain thing to strike with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.75,0:11:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was so it wouldn't splatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.84,0:11:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it, the PET bottle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.05,0:11:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they struck when the contents had been\Nfrozen solid, then the liquid wouldn't splatter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the culprit is the one who had a\Ncarbonated drink in a PET bottle, Arimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.10,0:11:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.18,0:11:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bzz. Bzz. Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came out of his room after 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.02,0:11:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, Inspector, and the other detectives\Nexamined the PET bottle before 7:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.57,0:11:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the air-conditioning in there, an hour\Nand a half wouldn't be enough time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.24,0:11:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the ice in a 500ml container to completely dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.37,0:11:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then what was it? That hard thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I think even you have some of them with you, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.88,0:11:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.13,0:11:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's something that everyone has with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.76,0:11:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a coin. Coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.47,0:11:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they were probably ten yen coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.85,0:11:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Ten yen coins?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.89,0:12:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young lady, how would you be able to strike someone a ten yen coin?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right: with a single ten yen coin, the best\Nyou could do would be to bruise someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.53,0:12:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you had something like 300 of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.49,0:12:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would become a mass of copper\Nweighing approximately 1.5 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.99,0:12:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, that's certainly true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.91,0:12:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one had such a large amount of{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.66,0:12:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They disposed of them after the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.17,0:12:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Disposed of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.17,0:12:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They put them in that machine behind you, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.34,0:12:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.51,0:12:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cigarette vending machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.22,0:12:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, they put 300 ten yen coins in a PET bottle and\Nused it as a bludgeon to beat the victim to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.35,0:12:41.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after the crime, they used the ten yen coins in the\Nvending machine and that's how they vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.02,0:12:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bzz. Bzz. Bzz.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.73,0:12:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mouth of a PET soda bottle is too small to fit ten yen coins in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.65,0:12:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you struck someone with something like that in it, both\Nthe interior and exterior of the PET bottle would be scratched.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.86,0:12:55.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd know right away if you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.62,0:12:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what the heck did they put them in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:13:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was something just like ten yen coins that everyone uses...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.12,0:13:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And furthermore, when you stuff a large\Nnumber of ten yen coins inside them...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.59,0:13:09.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They become a weapon that is commonly called a "blackjack."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.46,0:13:11.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Socks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.84,0:13:12.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Socks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.18,0:13:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.26,0:13:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honma Kyouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.89,0:13:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would it be him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.39,0:13:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both Tamai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} are wearing socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.69,0:13:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoes are kind of stretched tightly, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.95,0:13:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.66,0:13:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.74,0:13:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he mistakenly came into our room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.08,0:13:46.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He bumped into Arimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and fell down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, rather than being stretched\Ntight, his shoes were almost falling off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.30,0:13:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now he's wearing the second pair he used as the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.76,0:14:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably done to hide the sock he used at the\Ntime of the crime that has the victims blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.22,0:14:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Honma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had that carton of cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.27,0:14:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had the box for the carton with him beforehand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the pile of cigarettes he got when he disposed\Nof the ten yen coins in the vending machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.07,0:14:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could have been placed in the box in order to deceive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.61,0:14:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you check the pile of ten yen coins in the cigarette\Nvending machine, you will have your conclusive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.20,0:14:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If any blood got on the sock, then some\Nshould be on the ten yen coins inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.75,0:14:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they will have his fingerprints on them as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.00,0:14:35.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a culprit wanting to leave the scene\Nand use up the ten yen coins quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.23,0:14:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think he'd be wearing gloves or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.76,0:14:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then when you told us you hadn't seen\Nthe culprit, that was a lie, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.60,0:14:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not that you just saw him, you knew him well, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.77,0:14:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.94,0:14:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's name was Tatsumi. If you just hear that,\Nyou can't really tell if it was a man or a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.78,0:14:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.94,0:14:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said that if he had met the victim, it would\Nhave been either in the corridor or in the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.37,0:15:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if you would say that if you\Ndidn't know the victim was a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.00,0:15:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't have met a woman inside the\Nseparated men's and woman's restrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.38,0:15:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.72,0:15:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.93,0:15:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.56,0:15:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.89,0:15:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kidnapper's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.90,0:15:30.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kidnapper?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.06,0:15:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.36,0:15:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man kidnapped my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.28,0:15:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when he learned that I'd reported it to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.53,0:15:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.33,0:15:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My son, who was only four years old, and that, in retaliation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.17,0:15:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.46,0:15:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.30,0:16:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Detective, do you remember a kidnapping\Ncase a year ago from Okuho city?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.06,0:16:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I heard that they'd arrested a suspect\Nbut couldn't prosecute for lack of evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.48,0:16:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they never found the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.15,0:16:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that man used the same trick that I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.61,0:16:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you kept watching him, looking to\Nmeet in a place where you could use that trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.28,0:16:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, a place with a cigarette vending machine and private\Nrooms, like this karaoke box, so you could exact your revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.12,0:16:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.50,0:16:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you should be grateful to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.13,0:16:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From those pictures that man was taking, it\Nlooks like you would have been the next victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, with someone as perceptive as you,\Nyou probably wouldn't have been kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.89,0:16:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And your parents wouldn't have had\Nto do something as stupid as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.74,0:17:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That turned into a lousy celebration for your return, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.32,0:17:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, I was really impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s deduction show.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.16,0:17:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just like Sleeping Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.50,0:17:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your great deductions put even Shinichi to shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.25,0:17:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.25,0:17:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet I don't remember a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.55,0:17:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.07,0:17:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that high-school detective, Kudou Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.39,0:17:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, he's Ran's long distance husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.64,0:17:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.97,0:17:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got married as high-school students?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.93,0:17:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I haven't! Not with a guy like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.23,0:17:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been away for a long time, wrapped up in some case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.44,0:17:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like a lengthy separation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.61,0:17:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we're actually living together...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another book I want to buy, so you head home before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.12,0:17:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.24,0:17:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.37,0:17:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go with him and make sure he gets back to the detective office.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.97,0:18:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.01,0:18:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:08.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason you're deliberately coming with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.22,0:18:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something you want to discuss with me, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.97,0:18:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking about it and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.77,0:18:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've decided to go to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.81,0:18:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're going to enter the witness protection program?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.07,0:18:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, as you figured, I turned that down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.90,0:18:24.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like I said before...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.40,0:18:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate being restricted by anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.11,0:18:32.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, luckily, it looks like I have yet to draw the attention of\Nthe people from that evil organization you told me about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.29,0:18:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why are you going to America?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.33,0:18:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like my father and sister, I want to join the CIA!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll dig up and expose bad people and\Ntheir evil deeds out of every nook and cranny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.42,0:18:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And someday, my sister and I will bring down that evil Organization!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.43,0:18:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First of all you better fix that "clumsy kid"\Nproblem or you won't get into the CIA.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.18,0:18:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.06,0:18:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the CIA is an organization that acts\Non behalf of American national interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.94,0:19:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does this guy understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.48,0:19:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.86,0:19:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going, why did you come back to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.07,0:19:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if was just for a short time, I wanted to\Nsee my close friends before I went and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.33,0:19:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Confess my love to Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.62,0:19:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I fell in love with her from the first time I met her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.34,0:19:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd never met someone as pretty and kind as her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.76,0:19:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it seems that's she's in love with Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.30,0:19:33.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} thinks about her, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.39,0:19:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.35,0:19:38.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know how to contact Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.94,0:19:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could you ask him for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.02,0:19:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it would be all right to confess my love for Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.86,0:19:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'll never keep Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.45,0:19:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My plan is to bring her with me to America\Nsomeday so we can both live happily together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.58,0:20:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.33,0:20:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I wasn't asking for your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.55,0:20:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to ask Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.42,0:20:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm saying you can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.77,0:20:17.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.85,0:20:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You aren't saying you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.23,0:20:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.48,0:20:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.49,0:20:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That solves that mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.62,0:20:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason I went to see Detective Mouri in the first place was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.87,0:20:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I heard he'd met with Mizunashi\NRena just before she disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.17,0:20:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, I didn't know she was my sister and a CIA agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.01,0:20:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought for sure that Detective Mouri was one of\Nthe bad guys and was sheltering her somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.39,0:20:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I was looking into Detective Mouri on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.10,0:21:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, I figured something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.35,0:21:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His deduction power before and after he started\N"Sleeping Kogorou" was completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.44,0:21:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And at Sleeping Kogorou's side, there was always you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I couldn't think how you could have gotten smaller...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.99,0:21:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, you really are Kudou Shinichi, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.46,0:21:23.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.12,0:21:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You talk like you already knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.25,0:21:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'd guessed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.63,0:21:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around the time Sleeping Kogorou first appeared,\Nyou had taken an absence from school...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.59,0:21:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was one time that I fell down\Nnot from clumsiness, but on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.10,0:21:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You remember, it was the first time we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.18,0:21:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's great to meet you, Detective Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.39,0:21:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's such an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.19,0:21:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you did that just to grab on to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.07,0:21:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I really did fall in love with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.45,0:21:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please make her happy for my sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.75,0:23:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.00,0:23:26.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.46,0:23:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something seems to have happened with the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.79,0:23:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.05,0:23:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.00,0:23:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Based on their mood, it seems that someone might have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.22,0:23:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if they haven't told you about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.43,0:23:43.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.15,0:23:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.07,0:23:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there are zero requests today as well, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.74,0:24:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would be calling me at this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.04,0:24:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Codename...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.08,0:24:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bourbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.83,0:24:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's got to be one of those three who set the fire, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.76,0:24:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're here...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.51,0:24:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somewhere nearby...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.59,0:24:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A member of the Organization!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.87,0:24:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.27,0:24:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,DIARY
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.99,0:24:54.46,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode
